<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-945-616  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 945 616.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Dec 4 1989 v217 n24 p8(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC kills strategic pricing for special access, orders refunds.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Strategic pricing for custom services such as high-capacityprivate lines has been ruled out by the Federal CommunicationsCommission.andP;  The federal body ruled that while the practice wasneeded in the past, it has outlived its usefulness.andP;  Some localexchange carriers charged with pricing their services aboveprevious FCC guidelines will be ordered to make refunds.andO;Strategic pricing refers to the pricing of services based onfactors other than costs.andP;  In the past, the FCC had permitted theencouragement of some services through rate breaks that werecompensated by higher prices for others.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionTelephone CompaniesPricing PolicyOrdersCommunications Service Suppliers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>